The paper focuses on deep learning methods for completing and extrapolating portrait images, which involves tasks such as human body structure recovery and appearance synthesis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of perceptual loss and conditional adversarial loss, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper also mentions the potential application of the proposed framework to animal images, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
